{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17599405","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17599405"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:54:47+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:54:47+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15567"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15567","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15567"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8258"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70160"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8258","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8258"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15567"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55623"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4940"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"5103"},{"type":"tags","id":"7005"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19954"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19956"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70160","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70160"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe synthesis of thyroid hormones requires several enzymatic steps within thyroid follicular cells. Understanding this sequence is crucial for comprehending thyroid disorders.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best represents the correct sequence of steps in thyroid hormone synthesis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Trapping, proteolysis, oxidation, coupling, endocytosis, iodination, secretion","Trapping, oxidation, iodination, coupling, endocytosis, proteolysis, secretion","Endocytosis, trapping, proteolysis, iodination, oxidation, coupling, secretion","Trapping, iodination, oxidation, proteolysis, coupling, endocytosis, secretion","Endocytosis, oxidation, coupling, iodination, proteolysis, trapping, secretion"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct sequence of thyroid hormone synthesis involves seven distinct steps:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETrapping\u003C/strong\u003E: Active transport of iodide into follicular cells via the sodium-iodide symporter\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOxidation\u003C/strong\u003E: Conversion of iodide to active iodine by thyroid peroxidase\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIodination\u003C/strong\u003E: Addition of iodine to tyrosine residues on thyroglobulin\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECoupling\u003C/strong\u003E: Joining of iodotyrosines to form T3 and T4\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEndocytosis\u003C/strong\u003E: Uptake of iodinated thyroglobulin from colloid\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProteolysis\u003C/strong\u003E: Breakdown of thyroglobulin to release hormones\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003ESecretion: Release of T3 and T4 into bloodstream\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis sequence is essential for normal thyroid function. Each step requires specific enzymes and transport proteins. Defects in any step can lead to thyroid hormone deficiency.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Thyroid hormone synthesis occurs in 7 sequential steps: trapping, oxidation, iodination, coupling, endocytosis, proteolysis, and secretion.","Iodine trapping by the sodium-iodide symporter is the first essential step in thyroid hormone synthesis.","Thyroid peroxidase enzyme is essential for both the oxidation and organification steps of hormone synthesis."],"references":["Brent GA. Mechanisms of thyroid hormone action. J Clin Invest. 2012 Sep;122(9):3035-43. doi: 10.1172/JCI60047. Epub 2012 Sep 4. PMID: 22945636; PMCID: PMC3433956","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrine System: Netter Collection of Medical Illustrations: Endocrine System E-book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Wass, J. A., \u0026 Stewart, P. M. (Eds.). (2011). Oxford textbook of endocrinology and diabetes. Oxford University Press, USA"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55623"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15567"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55623","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/55623"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-13T20:20:26+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-13T20:21:23+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8258"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70160"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://